    <item>
      <title>Metabase is available as an add-on on Clever Cloud</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/changelog/2024/10-28-metabase-available/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>//localhost:1313/changelog/2024/10-28-metabase-available/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;After some weeks of testing, the Clever Cloud&amp;rsquo;s Metabase add-on, developed with &lt;a href=&#34;https://david.sferruzza.fr/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;David Sferruzza&lt;/a&gt;, is available in public beta. Thus, you can deploy the service, from &lt;a href=&#34;https://console.clever-cloud.com/users/me/addons/new&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Console&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;//localhost:1313/developers/api&#34; &gt;API&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/CleverCloud/clever-tools&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Clever Tools&lt;/a&gt;, and use it in minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s based on a Java application and a PostgreSQL database. Once deployed you&amp;rsquo;ll get a management URL to create an admin account. Then, just start using Metabase, add your data sources, create your questions and dashboards. You&amp;rsquo;ll get benefits from the Clever Cloud&amp;rsquo;s integration, with scalability options, database backups logs, metrics, easy version and upgrade management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feel free to let us know what you think and ask your questions in &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/CleverCloud/Community/discussions/categories/metabase&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;our GitHub Community&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;//localhost:1313/developers/doc/addons/metabase/&#34; &gt;Learn more about Metabase on Clever Cloud&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
